<TITLE> Shakib to undergo treatment in Australia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 27 (bdnews24.com)  Stand-in Bangladesh captain Shakib Al Hasan will travel to Australia next week for medical treatment on his groin, reports Cricinfo. "He has been in acute groin pain during the past one month and had to play with painkillers," Bangladesh Cricket Board spokesman Rabeed Imam said on Thursday. "He will fly to Australia next week where doctors will see his injury and decide whether to operate on him." Shakib stood in for injured Bangladesh captain Mashrafe Bin Mortaza and led the side to historic Test and ODI victories against the West Indies away from home, and followed it up with a 4-1 ODI series win in Zimbabwe. Shakib is the fifth Bangladesh bowler to get injured in recent months, after Mashrafe, fast bowler Rubel Hossain, Nazmul Hossain and spinner Abdur Ra
